-------------- regionalEffects ------------
Food instantly molders and water instantly evaporates when brought into the lair. Other nonmagical drinks are spoiled - wine turning into vinegar, for instance
Divination spells cast within the lair by creatures other than the mummy lord have a 25 percent chance to provice misleading results, as determined by the DM. If a divination spell already has a chance to fail or become unreliable when cast multiple times, that chance increases by 25 percent
A creature that takes treasure from the lair is cursed until the treasure is returned. The cursed target has disadvantage on all savin throws. The curse lasts until removed by a remove curse spell or other magic
